photos.description: E01 Shellrock looked a bit too humanoid for the judge's taste. Great work, but not quite "sea creature" enough.

E01 Even after Tina and Russ received a stern reprimand on their unprofessional behavior, someone had to be sent home. After their creature’s effective failure, it was destined to be either Chaz or Robert. Chaz drew the short straw, being the first of the designers sent home. We will miss you, Chaz. Good luck!【某些角度有点像……某人
E01 Lex and Josh were crowned the winning team, with Josh taking home the prize for this week’s challenge.
E01 Chaz and Robert weren’t quite as successful with “Floyd”. It was a little too cartoonish for the judges’ tastes, and a little too harrowing for the puppeteer to operate.
E01 But Josh and Lex’s devil prawn was the one to beat.
E01 Ben and Melissa’s creature wowed the judges from the beginning.
E01 After two days of grueling work, the designers were ready to have their creatures face the judges in the screen test.
E01 As they fabricated their prawn from the murky depths, Josh blew Lex away with what he could do with simple aluminum foil and hot glue.

E01 Tina and Russ were on a bumpy road from the beginning. Their deep, dark variation on an angler fish gave Russ problems from the beginning, but he wasn’t comfortable voicing his opinions with Tina’s tendency to keep talking.
E01 Melissa and Ben began working with how their puppeteer would get around in the creature suit, and then jammed on building their design up from there.

E01 The contestants were divided into five teams, and given their creature brief for the week. They had two days to bring to life a sea creature from an unseen sea floor three miles below the surface. Their creative mentor for the week? None other than Pete Brooke, the Shop’s creative supervisor.
E01 Kids, welcome to the candy store. When the contestants enter the Creature Shop for the first time, it’s a dream come true.好小
